.TH TETHERD 8 "May 2026" "Tether 0.1.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
tetherd \- Tether background daemon for iOS/Wayland integration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tetherd
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tetherd
 is a background daemon that manages the connection between a Linux Wayland
compositor and an iOS device running the Tether app. It handles clipboard
synchronization, file transfers, and secure device pairing using mTLS.

The daemon advertises its presence on the local network using mDNS (Bonjour)
and listens for incoming connections on TCP port 5134 by default. It also
provides a UNIX domain socket at \fB$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/tether/tetherd.sock\fR
for local communication with the \fBtether\fR(1) CLI and \fBtether-gtk\fR(1) GUI.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fB$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/tether/tetherd.sock\fR
The UNIX domain socket used for local communication.
.TP
\fB$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/tether/tetherd.lock\fR
Advisory lock file to ensure only one instance of the daemon is running.
.TP
\fB$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/tether/certs/\fR
Directory containing the mTLS certificates and keys.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tether (1),
.BR tether-gtk (1)
